title: Grateful Dead Live at Anaheim Stadium on 1987-07-26
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.6 MHz) >dBpoweramp > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Iko Iko, Minglewood Blues, Tons Of Steel, West L.A. Fadeaway, When I Paint My Masterpiece-> Mexicali Blues, Bird Song-> Promised Land

Set 2

Shakedown Street, Looks Like Rain, Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Jam-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away

Set 3

Mr. Tambourine Man, Dead Man, Maggie's Farm, Simple Twist Of Fate, Watching The River Flow, It's All Over Now Baby Blue, Chimes Of Freedom, Queen Jane Approximately, Stuck Inside Of Mobile With The Memphis Blues Again, Ballad Of A Thin Man, Rainy Day Women #12 And #35, Gotta Serve Somebody, All Along The Watchtower

Third set with Bob Dylan

reviews.review_text:
Thank you Mr. Charlie This recording is a blessing! If only I’d been born a few years earlier would have seen these guys live. Have seen all iterations of Dead, but there’s nothing like the real Deal. This show has me smiling ear to ear
✌️❤️⚡️💀✌️❤️

Great Memories! Thank you Charlie Miller and Archive.org for this. it was like my 10th or 15th show, but for whatever reason it was the first one where psychedelia entered my consciousness :-) I grew up in So Cal and was fairly familiar with the Big A Stadium, but that afternoon and evening stand out as being SO different in my mind. I love listening to the show and this is the best recording of it out there. Thank you!
